# Rust Style

- Use idiomatic, stable Rust with clear module boundaries.
- Prefer small modules and direct names over generic framework layers.
- Avoid unnecessary cloning; clone only when ownership clarity or async boundaries require it.
- Use `Result` types instead of panics in application logic.
- Use `thiserror` for domain errors.
- Use `anyhow` only at the binary/application startup boundary.
- Keep async functions readable and avoid blocking work inside handlers.
- Document structs and enums that represent public project concepts.
- Mentally run `cargo fmt` and `cargo clippy` when generating code.
- Add unit tests for business logic and integration tests for HTTP behavior.
